cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper discusses neural network models and their resource requirements, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the proposed method on image classification suggests that it could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of adaptive regularization function and the optimization of quantization depth could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on quantization and memory footprint could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
